text:
Q: Login session always remains true in Next.js, even after logout A: <p><code>session</code> is a <em><strong>defined</strong></em> function, so it is a <em><strong>truthy</strong></em> value, which is why the conditionally rendering always renders the logout UI and button.</p>
<p>I suspect you meant to <em>call</em> <code>session</code> at some point and save the returned value for whether or not the user is authenticated or not. I suggest a minor refactor to add some local React state to hold this value and a <code>useEffect</code> hook to issue the side-effect to check the user's authentication status.</p>
<p>Basic Example:</p>
<pre class="lang-js prettyprint-override"><code>export default function Navbar() {
  const [session, setSession] = React.useState();

  React.useEffect(() =&gt; {
    const checkSession = async () =&gt; {
      const session = await getSession();
      setSession(session);
    };

    checkSession();
  }, []);

  return (
    &lt;header&gt;
      &lt;nav className=&quot;box shadow-sm p-2&quot;&gt;
        &lt;div className=&quot;container mx-auto&quot;&gt;
          &lt;div className=&quot;flex justify-between&quot;&gt;
            &lt;Link href=&quot;/&quot; className=&quot;text-3xl text-blue-400 font-semibold font-theme&quot;&gt;
              Contact Manager
            &lt;/Link&gt;
            &lt;div className=&quot;flex justify-between items-center gap-2 text-blue-400 text-[1.6rem] font-theme&quot;&gt;
              {session ? (
                &lt;&gt;
                  &lt;Link href=&quot;/contact&quot;&gt;New Contact&lt;/Link&gt;
                  &lt;LogoutBtn /&gt;
                &lt;/&gt;
              ) : (
                &lt;Link href=&quot;/login&quot;&gt;Login&lt;/Link&gt;
              )}
            &lt;/div&gt;
          &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/nav&gt;
    &lt;/header&gt;
  );
}
</code></pre>
